<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-12-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-12-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="1173" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1173">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File. No. 312.52/61.</note>
                            <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-12-17">
                                        <hi rend="italic">December 17, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Earnestly use your unofficial good offices to secure protection for
                                properties of Spanish subjects who have been expelled from
                                Chihuahua.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
